Package com.twiceagain.selescript.runtime

Class FrameStack

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.twiceagain.selescript.runtime.FrameStack
  • public class FrameStack
extends java.lang.Object
    A class that maintains state within loops and provide loop management utilities. You typically have a single FrameStack per program. To start a new loop, you call prepare(). While loop(), you loop through the statements. When you are finished, you call cleanUp(). During the loop, you may start /cleanup nested loops. At anytime, you may get contextual info about the current WebElement, count, ...
    Author:
    xavier
